Initialize HealthCounts to non-null value.In a stress test I was doing that pounds a circuit immediately after creation it would have thread contention on the compareAndSet, one thread would go to create it, the other(s) would go to the else and return null and cause an NPE when trying to use it.nThe losing threads should get the originally initialized value set to 0.n

HystrixCollapser Refactor for PerformanceIllegalStateException: Future Not Started https://github.com/Netflix/Hystrix/issues/80nn- refactored HystrixTimer to be multi-threaded and use ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor to achieve thisn- refactored HystrixCollapser to:n  -- timeout on wait and trigger batch execution from calling thread instead of relying on only background timern  -- use single CountDownLatch per batch rather than 2 per collapsed requests to dramatically reduce number of items being waited onn  -- changed how batches are defined so the creation of a batch is a simpler step without a loop over all requests to register with the batchnnTesting on a production canary shows these changes have given significant efficiency and thus performance gains.n
Merge pull request #114 from benjchristensen/issue-80-feb25HystrixCollapser Refactor for Performance and Concurrency Bug Fixes

Version 1.3.6

BugFix: ConcurrencyStrategy.wrapCallable was not being used for reactive event-loop threads.The Rx Scheduler now correctly has state transferred to it with ConcurrencyStrategy.wrapCallable.nnNote that if the Rx sequence ever migrates to another thread (such as using observeOn) it is up to the user to deal with this as Hystrix loses control of the flow at that point.nnThis change does ensure though that the initial threads the callbacks are performed on has the expected thread context.nnThe design of this code is not very elegant and uses a workaround similar to posting variables on a stack before a method uses them. I have used this approach because I do not want to add a 'wrapFunc2' method to the ConcurrencyStrategy as the use of Func2 is just an implementation detail internally and the users of the library should not have to replicate the effort for both Callable and Func2. Thus the internal code is a little odd but the public API is untouched.n

BugFix: Race condition between run() and timeoutThis uses compareAndSet to synchronize timeout vs run() completion logic when there is a race.nnI have not been able to to replicate the issue reported at https://github.com/Netflix/Hystrix/issues/188 but I can see how the existing code is vulnerable to a race condition. This theoretically should fix it. All unit tests pass for existing functionality. All my attempts to create a unit test to reveal the issue failed.n

Handling InterruptedExceptions in the HystrixMetricsStreamServletSome environments like spring boots embedded Tomcat interrupt the worker threads on shutdown. Interupting a thread is the Java way to politely ask it to gracefully stop doing long running things. Since serving an event stream is a long running thing, we should stop sending the stream and stop polling, whenever an InterruptedException occures.n

Race condition exists when constructing a HystrixThreadPool where the ThreadPoolExecutor used by HystrixThreadPool.Factory is not the same instance as the one that is associated with the HystrixMetricsPublisherThreadPool. This causes a disconnect between the ThreadPoolExecutor's metrics and those supplied by HystrixMetricsThreadPool.Now the ThreadPoolExecutor itself is retrieved from the HystrixMetricsThreadPool object, because it is protected behind the pattern of a ConcurrentMap#putIfAbsent. This seemed much more difficult to do with the ConcurrencyStrategynas then any further custom implementations would not have similar concurrency guarantees.nnA test has been added to show that the ThreadPoolExecutor construct is indeed correct and the same as the one associated with the metrics publisher. It was a bit difficult to construct a test to prove the bad case and good case at the same time. Once the solution was in place, I had to turn the failing test case into a validation test case.nnIn addition this exposed some static state that was kept around between some tests that needed to be cleaned up. In particular the HystrixMetricsPublisherFactory has a singleton object that needed to be reset (even though it's a singleton) in order to validate the test. I'm not particularly happy with this approach, so I'd be happy for any help here.nnConflicts:nthystrix-core/src/test/java/com/netflix/hystrix/HystrixThreadPoolTest.javan

Use Archaius for Hystrix plugin setupCurrently, Hystrix lets you define custom strategies in two ways:n1) with System propertiesn2) with bootstrapping via HystrixPlugins.getInstance().registerXXXnIf neither is specified, the default strategy is used.nnThis change replaces hardwired System.getProperty calls with lookupnvia Archaius. So one can override the plugin strategies used withnany configuration provider Archaius is configured with.nnMost importantly, it has the effect of checking any file callednconfig.properties on the classpath as well as using system properties.nThis lets you configure plugin strategies without having to writenJava code for it, or having to run the application with additionalnsystem properties.nnFixes #92n

Load configuration from hystrix-plugins.properties as wellIf the file hystrix-plugins.properties exists on the class path, itsnconfiguration will be used to setup HystrixPlugins.nnThis makes it possible to bundle bootstrap configuration for Hystrixnin higher-level libraries without polluting the global namespace withna 'config.properties' file; that name should better be reservednfor top-level applications only.n
